title: White Wall
description:
Beat by: @digitalluc
Produced by: @Jfresh130 at The Mobile Recording Studio

"White wall white wall when do you predict my fall
Ive failed every little thing that ive sworn
Ive lost a lot, the gains seem so little
Bonds are unbreakable yet mine seem so brittle
In the middle, which path leads back home
Why, why do they laugh so, cause of the gastro
If i made mad dough and reach for the astros
Could they still belittle, with they gats froze
Merely a scenario, i still lack those
Wanting the whole package, yet you still lactose
Youre here to keep me safe, but are you to keep me sane
Two sides of a coin with results you cant complain
Will you still ignore me, and paint me with your plain
Or will you adore me, and keep me from the pain
I present my case to these four horsemen
Why do i hide my face, its to at least keep a portion
A precaution

Thats the way the paint dries
Symbolizing tears that pour down from my eyes
But why cry, i hide behind like a shy-guy
Looking to be noticed but never in the primetime
Silent is my audience, I ask if you exist
Tomatoes born from nothing til i make an exit
White wall White wall why so petty
You contain so much yet im still so empty

White wall white wall why no answer
I confide to you my emotional financer
Emotions are black, is that maybe the reason
Define as treason for betraying my favourite season
Coat the world in pure, how can i endure
When i dont belong in a world so sure
Confidence is key, yet i lack the lock
Maybe take the lead, and give the door a knock
No jiggle on the handle life in a standstill
Cuffed to an anvil and told to stand still
You have to wait your turn to join the landfill
Avoid the trample, ease with an advil
Vision blurred already, out fades the medley 
Who knew that silence could feel this heavy
White wall white wall i bid farewell
My silent adviser, i descend the stairwell"

"Norwegian jazz hip hop producer Ol' Burger Beats is following up his critically acclaimed (and sold out) debut album "High Rhodes LP" with "Unreleased Instrumentals". It's a 12" mini-album including 8 previously unreleased beats. description:
thank you for ALL the support

music video: http://bit.ly/2yaRgA1


I like to think I‚Äôm well-equipped as any other average guy 
but I just can‚Äôt discover love and I don‚Äôt even set my standards high
on top of that, I‚Äôm camera shy, maybe I should opt-out of the dating pool
and be an undercover tinder samurai

cause I would rather type online than whisper in a dingy bar
and swiping left and right could be my new bushido ninja star
and I‚Äôm well-versed in virtual lovemaking ninjutsu 
on every profile pic I post, I‚Äôm posing with my shitzu
or flexing with my shirt off cause I heard that gets you hits too

Especially OkCupid, I‚Äôm like Eros or the cherubs be,
I pierce hearts of women with my cursor and my arrow keys
and disregard my Roman roots and choose a font that‚Äôs serif-free,

trust me,

 I‚Äôm a tinder bio brainiac
the way I kindle fire with matches, I‚Äôm a pyromaniac
on christian mingle, I‚Äôm a casanova,
if ya‚Äôll don‚Äôt think so, y‚Äôall can ask Jehovah
check your inbox, he might send an answer over

I wish I had the muscles of a granite sculpture
I would log on ashleymadison and bang adulterers
I‚Äôm so lonely, I‚Äôve considered farmers-only
just for someone‚Äôs arms to hold me
also, I‚Äôm really big on agriculture

but if I had that body of a grecian god
I would trawl on pof.com and use it as a fishing rod
and hope I don‚Äôt get catfish,
the fact is if I did, I‚Äôd probably play along cause god knows I could use the practice,

and if I‚Äôm aching for my roots, I‚Äôd visit shaadi.com
message islamic wahhabi hijabi hotties ‚Äúsalaam‚Äù
and sunni, shia, those are both denominations I respect
cause I just care for our connection, 

I don‚Äôt care about the sects

sometimes I uninstall my apps in reckless insurrectious rage
and then regret it while I check the craiglist missed connections page
and then I think that I should get out more and disregard my mobile cell
and get to know the local teller at my barnes and noble well
and check out what she‚Äôs reading while she‚Äôs charging up my total sale
and ask her if she likes the novel,
and once she answers, ask her if wants to grab some coffee or some ice cream waffles,
and she‚Äôd probably say that‚Äôs awesome, 

 I‚Äôd ask her when she‚Äôs off of work,

 she might answer ‚Äúmidnight‚Äù

 I‚Äôd tell her that sounds awful, 

what a bummer, and from somewhere
I might muster up the nerve to get her number,

 and I would ask her what her digits are
and if I play it right then I can disregard my ninja stars, 
say sayonara to katanas and my other weapons too 
and try committing by committing online dating seppuku

title: Baltra - Feds Watching (B1)
description:
Purchase here: http://www.juno.co.uk/products/baltra-short-term-goals/639952-01/

Hailing from the hazy streets of NYC, Baltra's trademark sounds have been pleasing the ears of ravers and recliners alike and appeared on just about every dance music list worth a dime at the conclusion of 2016. With recent releases on labels such as Craigie Knowes and Hokkaido Dance Club, Tape Throb are honoured to bring Short Term Goals to vinyl and to contribute to the rise and rise of this talented producer. Think throbbing drums and universal chords with that trademark Baltra warmth that keeps you coming back for more. Ethereal vocals dance on punchy base and silky refrains give you just enough time to catch your breath. All the radiating warmth of house, with all the reminders that you are experiencing something seminal, these are beats on the cusp.

title: 100% Electronica Presents: S U R F I N G - Lifetime
description:
It is my great pleasure to announce  S U R F I N G's classic debut "Deep Fantasy" is available on vinyl, exclusively from 100% Electronica. In June we released a pressing of 400, which sold out in less than 12 hours. Due to overwhelming demand, we have reissued it as a run of 800. And its available right now!

Thank you to S U R F I N G for creating a masterpiece, and thank you to the supporters who have allowed me to turn my vinyl-wish-list into reality. I look forward to helping create more beautiful records though this outlet in the future. It is an honor to have "Deep Fantasy" be the first 100% Electronica album not created in-house.

"Deep Fantasy" is available on limited vinyl now at www.100percentelectronica.com

Black virgin vinyl
limited pressing of 800

hey so this is my first project. its a collection of tracks made & selected mostly over the last few months.

hope you enjoy <3

1. intro w @byrook1e 
2. i still dont know who i am

7. my friends

description:
in.the.forest.we.are.wizards is an ep about childhood nostalgia. about places that no longer exist, people who are no longer with us, endless summer days filled with mystery and wonder.. personally, playing the piano brings back so many memories, and that is one of the reasons why I chose this ep to be so piano driven..

hopefully you can enjoy and relax to this one... if you want to talk about anything, just drop me a msg..

i am eternally grateful to you grandma for all those days we got to hang out at your place when we were kids. <3

love, KUPLA

title: Cookin Soul & FS Green - Rooftop
description:
@cookinsoul @fsgreen

'College Music Presents: Back on Track' is a twenty nine track compilation featuring original music from artists and producers the world over. 'Back on Track' aims to act as a beacon of hope after a tricky few years across the world. College Music Records have carefully selected a wide range of artists to feature on the project, spanning from UK, America, Europe and beyond. The end result is a wide array of uplifting vibes, from instrumental beats and jazzy joints to euphoric vocal breakbeats and lo-fi house, featuring the likes of Tennyson, Cookin Soul, Athletic Progression, L'ind√©cis, edbl and a lot more.

Listen to the compilation on all platforms:
‚Üí cmrecords.co.uk/back-on-track

The artwork itself, done by the incredible Doug John Miller (http://instagram.com/dougjohnmiller) reflects the journey from the darker, lockdown days to present day and beyond, where things are looking far brighter. We aimed to represent this positive shift in the music selected within the project, hoping to offer a glimmer of light to people in their dark days.

The project title ' Back on Track' reflects how things have come off the rails in the past few years, but that better times are on the way, and as a collective, we are gradually getting 'Back on Track'.

Thank you for listening!

title: Cookin Soul & FS Green - Rooftop
description:
@cookinsoul @fsgreen

'College Music Presents: Back on Track' is a twenty nine track compilation featuring original music from artists and producers the world over. 'Back on Track' aims to act as a beacon of hope after a tricky few years across the world. College Music Records have carefully selected a wide range of artists to feature on the project, spanning from UK, America, Europe and beyond. The end result is a wide array of uplifting vibes, from instrumental beats and jazzy joints to euphoric vocal breakbeats and lo-fi house, featuring the likes of Tennyson, Cookin Soul, Athletic Progression, L'ind√©cis, edbl and a lot more.

Listen to the compilation on all platforms:
‚Üí cmrecords.co.uk/back-on-track

The artwork itself, done by the incredible Doug John Miller (http://instagram.com/dougjohnmiller) reflects the journey from the darker, lockdown days to present day and beyond, where things are looking far brighter. We aimed to represent this positive shift in the music selected within the project, hoping to offer a glimmer of light to people in their dark days.

The project title ' Back on Track' reflects how things have come off the rails in the past few years, but that better times are on the way, and as a collective, we are gradually getting 'Back on Track'.

Thank you for listening!

title: PREMIERE : Trudge - Give
description:
Axe On Wax's Axe Traxx drops its second hand-stamped vinyl only release, a split EP featuring originals from Trudge and Die Roh.
After the well received first release, Axe Traxx returns with another collection of rough, raw, filtered house killer tracks. The first EP from Sonderr and remixed by Mall Grab (both Australian) was supported by many in the scene and this split EP showcases two different approaches to analogue productions. The raw in your face filtered House of Parisian talent Trudge and the always splendidly crafted grooves of Sagat and DJ octopus, aka Die Roh. Trudge's 'Give' sounds like a mix between Mall Grab and Ross From Friends, between Churches and Lobster Theremin: a distorted and in part broken 909 beat guides the cut, whilst a slow melodic loved up vocal creates the perfect summery vibe.  The limited 180g vinyl Axe Traxx 2 is out in late July !

title: PREMIERE : Slim Hustla - 2100
description: Second release at Nerang Recordings is jam packed with floor moving goodies. Subjoi starts us off on a journey with his track Signal Point, bring your moon boots. Interplanetary Criminal backs that up with Softly, his own unique spice rack of a track. On the B-side here premiered, we have Slim Hustla with their track 2100. No intros needed, Slim has been destroying the northern part of our globe so it was time to bring em' down under. Jesse Bru closes the show with his emotion packed track Mustard King, warm and tasty, Al Dente.

title: XK005 | Slim Steve - Bedroom Jams EP
description:
Joining the X-Kalay roster for his debut EP, Slim Steve delivers four impressive cuts of infectious, lust infused house. Produced on an array of hardware in Steve‚Äôs bedroom in Rome, this is a refreshingly honest EP and takes the label into somewhat nostalgic territory. 

90‚Äôs ballads meet sampled italo percussion, skittish pitched up vocals pierce dangerous basslines and lung busting breakdowns give way to searching lasers in smoke filled rooms. English born Italian Steve Langrish accomplishes all this with a level of effortlessness that belies his astonishingly young years. 

An impressive debut for sure. Watch this space ‚Äì Slim‚Äôs comin!

title: Elyon - Andante [Lo-fi]
description:
A friend and I were talking about "Lo-fi" hiphop genre and about how it's becoming "popular" again. I personally enjoy listening to this genre but never tried creating something in it. "Lo-fi," meaning "Low Fidelity," adds that "gritty" and "low quality" sound that used to be all around us in the 90's and before. Now days, everything's HQ or HD, we have CDs instead of cassette tapes or vinyls, DVD players or online streaming instead of VHS players. I had a warm fuzzy feeling inside as I was creating this. It reminded me of my childhood, back when everything was "ordinary" and "innocent."

The word andante simply means "moderately slow tempo." Time has been moving way too fast for me, lately. It's time to take a little breather and refresh. Looking back, though tough, I had a really nice and a blessing of a childhood. Something that I'll never be able to relive and experience. I have to thank God for always being there, guiding me. Though I forget His presence and though I sometimes lose track of where I'm suppose to go, He never failed to show me His grace and patient love. I wish I could be more loving and caring like Him. I wish I could be a better friend to my friends. I wish I could be a better person. But the day of sunrise is nigh. Thank you to everyone who's been talking to me and checking up on me. Thank you for even sending me some encouraging words regarding music or life. I appreciate every one of you guys, supporting me in my musical endeavors.

Thank you everyone for supporting me on Patreon. Every dollar helps and with that being said, this song would not have been possible if it wasn't for your support! If you're not sure what Patreon is, here's a link with some information. If you wish to support me, consider becoming my patron in Patreon today! title: such nice sounds (prod. mt. marcy)
description:
@mt-marcy

LYRICS:
i'm sick of trembling in fear at the idea of death
since it's always on my mind i just hide in my bed
"everybody's scared of it" is what my therapist said
but my case seems worse, when i've barely been fed

because the kitchen's too far to desire the steps
it'd take to make it down the stairs and try to find a baguette
or something similar that wouldn't make my stomach upset
it doesn't feel like this is real, yeah, my mind is a mess

the only times it seems clear is when music is played
some relatable creator says i'll soon be okay
or when reading poetry trying to soothe the dismay
and i can lose my insecurities in cute little sayings, like

"why frown when the sun goes down,
if you'll wake in the morning to such nice sounds
when the nighttime creeps, well your eyes might weep
but that's just moonlight tryna find nice people"

"why frown when the sun comes 'round
even if you feel shaken or upside down
when the daytime hits, you'll be great, my friend
just make it through this, just make it through this"

"why frown when the sun comes 'round
even if you feel shaken or upside down
when the daytime hits, you'll be great, my friend
just make it through this, you can make it through this"

title: internet personas (prod. aimless)
description:
@aimless-beats

hey, everyone is someone at least a little bit different online
don't be scared to be honest, okay?
love you
<3

LYRICS:
we all got internet personas
internet personas we hide behind
we hide behind

we all got demons deep inside us
demons deep inside us we try to hide
we try to hide

i forgot who it is i truly am long ago
but i'll keep searching for it while i can

i knew a boy who could outline a shape in a second
that's display was eclectic in a way that was second to none
he had a hand than swam like fish in the seas
and a penstroke that'd bring any critic to his knees
it was beautiful, flowing like the blood inside my artieries
he painted hearts as targets and was practicing his archery
mastering the artistry he carried in his chest
until at best it was a godsend, and worst, it was a part of me
'til suddenly... things began to seem different
moods dissipated into blue and grey pigments
but surface-wise his screen names were never inefficient
as a method to communicate that happiness was with him
so a couple thousand people saw a perfectly inoccuous complexion
while i was tryna talk him through depression
the lesson to be learned is that your heros aren't invincible
just normal folks who often need expression, so pause and leave a message...

if you want; they'd probably appreciate it...

...internet personas
internet personas we hide behind
we hide behind

we all got demons deep inside us
demons deep inside that we try to hide
we try to hide

i forgot who it is i truly am long ago
but i'll keep searching for it while i can

i knew a person who could cultivate the words that they aligned
in a way that could coerce a train to fly
a perfect state of mind in which to learn creative rhymes
until their person was emburdened by the verses they designed
and they began to lose their touch...
the little quirks in all their writing became terse and uninviting
and ingesting any lettering they surgeoned into life
instead of being entertainment was inert and just absurd and all the work was fucking tiring
and suddenly... they were writing less and less
in spite of their success they saw no light and second guessed
the creativity they harbored in their heart
there's only so much fucking artwork you can make 'til you forget the way to start
so a couple million people saw some dipping in the frequency
of music while they fought idiosyncracy
that slept as mental illness... and woke as some peculiar train of thought
that masqueraded as a symptom of a hindering deliquency

i hope that all these words have made you think of me

internet personas, internet personas
we all got internet personas, internet personas (x7)

title: [winter in kyoto lp] w/ oxela
description:
When I first met @oxelaman111 we nerded out about each other's sounds for a good 20 min. We then quickly began to work on a project together which we called "springtime in prague." one of the main things we loved about instrumental hip hop was that it can transport you to somewhere else and can truly be the soundtrack to your life. 

now 9 months later we release the 2nd installment of our joint efforts. we lovingly present to you "winter in kyoto" an lp. we hope this takes you exactly where you want to go. 

so fucking thankful to everyone that listens. so much love.

1. now and again
2. 96 game boy
3. love me tomorrow
4. paradise city
5. lan rover
6. seven stars
7. the tunnel

Art hand done by the incredibly talented @mantis-hands

title: Gaijin II Tale of Rai Â§ñ‰∫∫  [Full LP]
description:
Gai-jin  -  (noun) Foreigner / Outsider

It‚Äôs been a year and 3 months since the foreigner arrived at the Land of the Samurai.

The epic sequel continues where our young hero Rai is on a quest to find his way back home and regain his memories that he once lost. Learning the way of the samurai, Rai has become highly skilled in his swordsmanship under the tutelage of Hachiro Sensei. Rai has matured but understands that there is plenty more room for growth. During this time on top of the vibrant Yama no aki, Hachiro reveals some clues in regards to how he can return home.


He explains that in order for him to go back home, he would have to face the shogun of this land in a 1-on-1 duel. That‚Äôs all he is able to share, but what Hachiro and Rai don‚Äôt know is that the shogun is also a foreigner and as to who the foreigner is, well‚Ä¶it happens to be Rai brother.

Gai-jin -(Noun) foreigner.

A tale about a foreigner who woke up in a mysterious land covered in mist.

As he was looking at his surroundings he bumped into a kid named Riku who had a broken wooden sword, Riku was excited because he'd never met a foreigner before. Riku later invited him to his home and the foreigner met his family but...this was no ordinary family as they were Samurais. 

As the foreigner peeked through the branchy hut he saw a dozen more just like Riku‚Äôs family, it was at that moment he realised he was in the Land of the Samurai.....

visuals by @user-itami: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1v102TPRwqE

track 2 of long days.short years | may 2017

inspired by a poem by nickki nguyen:

when you're waiting for something, or someone, you wrestle with this feeling of uncertainty and hopelessness. 
your days grow longer because you're just going through the motions and looping through the same unanswered questions, the same thoughts over and over. 
the worst part is that I didn't even realize I was doing it until it all came crashing down on me. 
i followed someone onto a train, but i didn't want to get off without him. 
so I waited. 
i grew impatient, anxious and unhappy. 
will it be this stop? 
or the next? 
maybe the one after. 
i kept hoping to get off. 
it's no wonder i didn't enjoy the actual train ride.
i didn't sit and look out the window and watch the world speed by. 
instead, i stared at the exit and the growing gap between me and him. 
in the end, i couldn't wait anymore. 
i got off.

long days without you here
short years with you there

internet personas (prod. aimless)
description:
@aimless-beats

hey, everyone is someone at least a little bit different online
don't be scared to be honest, okay?
love you
<3

LYRICS:
we all got internet personas
internet personas we hide behind
we hide behind

we all got demons deep inside us
demons deep inside us we try to hide
we try to hide

i forgot who it is i truly am long ago
but i'll keep searching for it while i can

i knew a boy who could outline a shape in a second
that's display was eclectic in a way that was second to none
he had a hand than swam like fish in the seas
and a penstroke that'd bring any critic to his knees
it was beautiful, flowing like the blood inside my artieries
he painted hearts as targets and was practicing his archery
mastering the artistry he carried in his chest
until at best it was a godsend, and worst, it was a part of me
'til suddenly... things began to seem different
moods dissipated into blue and grey pigments
but surface-wise his screen names were never inefficient
as a method to communicate that happiness was with him
so a couple thousand people saw a perfectly inoccuous complexion
while i was tryna talk him through depression
the lesson to be learned is that your heros aren't invincible
just normal folks who often need expression, so pause and leave a message...

if you want; they'd probably appreciate it...

...internet personas
internet personas we hide behind
we hide behind

we all got demons deep inside us
demons deep inside that we try to hide
we try to hide

i forgot who it is i truly am long ago
but i'll keep searching for it while i can

i knew a person who could cultivate the words that they aligned
in a way that could coerce a train to fly
a perfect state of mind in which to learn creative rhymes
until their person was emburdened by the verses they designed
and they began to lose their touch...
the little quirks in all their writing became terse and uninviting
and ingesting any lettering they surgeoned into life
instead of being entertainment was inert and just absurd and all the work was fucking tiring
and suddenly... they were writing less and less
in spite of their success they saw no light and second guessed
the creativity they harbored in their heart
there's only so much fucking artwork you can make 'til you forget the way to start
so a couple million people saw some dipping in the frequency
of music while they fought idiosyncracy
that slept as mental illness... and woke as some peculiar train of thought
that masqueraded as a symptom of a hindering deliquency

i hope that all these words have made you think of me

internet personas, internet personas
we all got internet personas, internet personas (x7)

title: Eli & Fur - Wild Skies
description:
Buy/Stream: https://anjunadeep.ffm.to/effitw.pbt
Listen to Anjunadeep New Releases: https://anjunadeep.ffm.to/newreleases.oyd
Discover the Anjunadeep Discography: https://anjunadeep.ffm.to/discog.oyd
Listen to Anjunadeep Radio 24/7: https://anjunadeep.ffm.to/radio
Release Date: 11th May 2021

----

Eliza Noble and Jennifer Skillman are Eli & Fur: the British live act, singer-songwriter and producer duo whose career together stretches back for nearly a decade. Having formed a close bond in their teens born out of their unwavering passion for music in all its guises, their careers as DJs, songwriters, vocalists and producers has taken them around the globe as touring musicians and seen them grace the stages of the biggest festivals in the world including Coachella, Tomorrowland and Glastonbury. 

‚ÄòFound In The Wild‚Äô is the pair‚Äôs long-awaited studio debut which will be released this summer on seminal electronic imprint and long-time label home Anjunadeep on 25th June. A dual part album concept, ‚ÄòFound in The Wild‚Äô is a sonic presentation of two contrasting and quintessential parts of the unique Eli & Fur sound; two sides of the Eli & Fur which they are finally ready to share with the world, ‚ÄúWe wanted to show both sides of us. We are quite varied in the way that we write music and so it made sense to have two parts living side by side. Everything we really love is on the album and we‚Äôre super proud of how it‚Äôs come together‚Äù. 

The first half of the album ‚ÄòFound‚Äô is a collection of song-based productions which show Eli & Fur‚Äôs strengths as songwriters, vocalists and producers in equal measure. Having begun their careers as songwriters at renowned production house Xenomania writing hits for pop acts like Girls Aloud, Eli & Fur‚Äôs talents as songwriters are abundantly clear. 

Released today, ‚ÄòWild Skies‚Äô is taken from the ‚ÄòFound‚Äô collection - a sensual and otherworldly ensemble which glues the duo‚Äôs trademark textured sound palette together perfectly. "Wild Skies came together so organically and naturally. I felt like I was expressing myself without even really realising how and the melodies just fell out of me. A lot of the time, I‚Äôll write lyrics before the song, but with this one there was no preparation whatsoever, I just sat down at the computer with the microphone and sung, and that was that!‚Äù (Fur).  

The second half of the LP ‚ÄòIn the Wild‚Äô is a change in gear conceptually and ventures into the more upbeat, clubbier side of the project - these tracks explore the girls‚Äô penchant for emotive productions geared for the dancefloor which find the sweet spot between the dark and the emotive, marrying evocative vocals written around their own experiences as young musicians with their unique brand of euphoric club cuts. Presented side by side as ‚ÄòFound In The Wild‚Äô, the first album from Eli & Fur shows the artists at their most assured.

About College Music:
At College Music, we find and showcase the latest work from up and coming artists. Whether you're about to go out, having a party or just relaxing; we aim to represent something exciting, attractive and inviting. The name originated because a small group of friends while at college struggled to find music which had originality and didn't conform to the generic "pop" which was consistently released to the public. College Music is about new music from unheard artists and providing a platform for them to be heard by listeners like us. We firmly believe that a brand‚Äôs name, ethos, and content should all align together. For us, our name ties in perfectly.

title: H A P P I N N E S   &   S A D N E S S
It's a Magical World (feat. Alcoda)
description:
Hello all, this is the second track off my 2nd tape with @alcoda777
Thanks to everyone who gave love to "the days are just packed", it means a lot to us. A few updates:
1. collab tape with @boppersboppers coming soon
2. new logo/cover photo/cover art out now. I chose an elephant because the first time i picked up a Calvin and Hobbes book, the first story was about Calvin turning himself into an elephant, as well as the fact that my favorite childhood movie was Babar, and lastly because I'm quite chubby in real life. It just seemed like the perfect thing to represent my music. Most of my art is done by De'Angelo Galvan. 
3. I have some experimental solo stuff coming soon. I've been real busy with life but I want to try to push beyond the boundaries of my own music and make something new and interesting. 

Thank you
-kal.kal
